{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015fMoVvXY2JrRAJMNgtENMZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# RNG Utopia — Contributor Guide\n     2→\n     3→This file is auto-loaded by Claude Code. All contributors (human or AI) must follow these rules.\n     4→\n     5→## Who Owns What\n     6→\n     7→This repo is the **code monorepo**. A separate root repo (not accessible to contributors) holds:\n     8→- Authoritative scope, decisions, and phase boundaries\n     9→- Spec checklists and implementation tracking\n    10→- Verification scripts and project governance\n    11→\n    12→**You can modify any file in this repo**, but you must follow the rules below.\n    13→\n    14→## Changelog Protocol (Mandatory)\n    15→\n    16→Every batch of work must update `CHANGELOG.md` at the repo root **before committing**.\n    17→\n    18→Format — append to the top of the Unreleased section:\n    19→\n    20→```markdown\n    21→### YYYY-MM-DD — [Short title]\n    22→**Author**: [name or agent identifier]\n    23→**Scope**: [which areas: docs, platform UI, game-engine, wallet, solana programs, etc.]\n    24→**Changes**:\n    25→- [file or area] — [what changed and why]\n    26→- [file or area] — [what changed and why]\n    27→**Breaking**: [yes/no — did you rename exports, change constants, restructure directories?]\n    28→**Terminology**: [list any term renames, e.g., \"cashback → rakeback\"]\n    29→```\n    30→\n    31→If `CHANGELOG.md` doesn't exist yet, create it with an `# Changelog` header and `## Unreleased` section.\n    32→\n    33→Why: The implementation team merges from this repo periodically. The changelog is how they know what to review and reconcile. Skipping it means changes may be reverted.\n    34→\n    35→## Locked Decisions (Do Not Change Without Coordination)\n    36→\n    37→These are settled. Changing them silently will cause merge conflicts and rework.\n    38→\n    39→| Decision | Current Value | Notes |\n    40→|----------|--------------|-------|\n    41→| Program architecture | Standard Anchor (`#[program]`) | NOT BOLT ECS |\n    42→| Program location | `solana/programs/` | Do not move to root `programs/` |\n    43→| Wallet approach | `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` | No Privy until post-V1 |\n    44→| Fee total | 3% (300 bps) | Hardcoded on-chain |\n    45→| Fee split | 200 rev / 70 rakeback / 30 chest | See terminology below |\n    46→| VRF provider | MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF | For coinflip |\n    47→| FE entrypoint | `apps/platform/` | Other app dirs are scaffolds |\n    48→| Package manager | pnpm | With turborepo |\n    49→\n    50→If you believe a locked decision should change, add a proposal file to `docs/proposals/` instead of changing the code directly.\n    51→\n    52→## Canonical Terminology\n    53→\n    54→Use these terms consistently in code, comments, docs, and UI labels.\n    55→\n    56→| Correct | Incorrect / Deprecated |\n    57→|---------|----------------------|\n    58→| rakeback pool | cashback pool, daily cashback |\n    59→| chest treasury | rewards budget, daily rewards |\n    60→| RAKEBACK_BPS / RAKEBACK_POOL_BPS | CASHBACK_BPS / CASHBACK_POOL_BPS |\n    61→| CHEST_TREASURY_BPS / CHEST_BPS | REWARDS_BUDGET_BPS / REWARDS_BPS |\n    62→| Emerald (tier 5) | Platinum |\n    63→| champion (avatar, Lv30) | cavalier |\n    64→\n    65→If you introduce new terminology, document it in the changelog entry.\n    66→\n    67→## Verification Requirements\n    68→\n    69→Before committing, you **must** pass:\n    70→\n    71→```bash\n    72→pnpm lint        # zero errors (warnings OK)\n    73→pnpm build:all   # all packages and apps build\n    74→```\n    75→\n    76→If you modify Solana programs (`solana/` directory), also run:\n    77→\n    78→```bash\n    79→cd solana && cargo check --workspace   # Rust compiles\n    80→```\n    81→\n    82→Do **not** commit if these fail. If you cannot fix a failure you introduced, revert your changes and document the issue in the changelog.\n    83→\n    84→## File Modification Guidelines\n    85→\n    86→### Visual changes — just do it\n    87→CSS, layout, styling, animations, static assets, avatar images, responsive breakpoints. These are low-risk. Make the change, note it in the changelog, commit.\n    88→\n    89→- `apps/platform/src/index.css` and component-scoped styles\n    90→- `apps/platform/public/` — static assets, images\n    91→- Component JSX structure (when purely visual — moving elements, changing labels)\n    92→- `packages/ui/` — shared UI components (visual only)\n    93→\n    94→### Logic / functionality changes — write a proposal first\n    95→Any change that affects **how the game works**, **what gets calculated**, or **what data flows where** must go through a proposal before implementation.\n    96→\n    97→Write a short PRD-style proposal to `docs/proposals/YYYY-MM-DD-title.md`:\n    98→\n    99→```markdown\n   100→# Proposal: [Title]\n   101→**Date**: YYYY-MM-DD\n   102→**Author**: [name or agent]\n   103→**Area**: [which game/system]\n   104→\n   105→## Problem\n   106→[What's wrong or missing]\n   107→\n   108→## Proposed Change\n   109→[What you want to change — be specific about files, functions, constants]\n   110→\n   111→## Impact\n   112→[What else this affects — other packages, on-chain programs, types]\n   113→\n   114→## Breaking\n   115→[yes/no — does this rename exports, change constants, alter game rules?]\n   116→```\n   117→\n   118→Do NOT implement the change — just write the proposal. The implementation team will review, approve, and integrate.\n   119→\n   120→Examples of \"logic changes\" that need proposals:\n   121→- Changing fee percentages, tier amounts, or XP formulas\n   122→- Adding/removing game phases or settlement steps\n   123→- Modifying payout calculations or reward distribution\n   124→- Restructuring shared type definitions or package exports\n   125→- Changing wallet connection flow or transaction signing\n   126→- Adding new on-chain instructions or modifying existing ones\n   127→\n   128→### Docs and specs — free to modify (follow terminology)\n   129→- `docs/` — game specs, platform docs, stories\n   130→- Follow the canonical terminology table above\n   131→- Note significant content changes in the changelog\n   132→\n   133→### Shared packages — modify with care\n   134→These are imported across packages. Renaming exports or changing shapes breaks consumers.\n   135→\n   136→- `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts` — type definitions and constants\n   137→- `packages/game-engine/src/index.ts` — public API surface\n   138→- `packages/wallet/src/` — wallet provider and hooks\n   139→- `packages/config/` — shared config\n   140→- `packages/fairness/` — fairness verification logic\n   141→\n   142→Rules for shared packages:\n   143→- **Visual/display changes** (label text, formatting) — OK, just changelog it\n   144→- **Logic/data changes** (constants, formulas, type shapes, exports) — write a proposal\n   145→- **Do not delete exports** — deprecate first, note in changelog\n   146→\n   147→### OFF LIMITS — Smart contracts and on-chain code\n   148→\n   149→**Do not modify, create, delete, rename, or restructure any file in these directories. No exceptions.**\n   150→\n   151→- `solana/` — ALL contents: Anchor programs, Rust crates, Cargo files, deploy scripts, tests, configs\n   152→- `packages/anchor-client/` — generated types from on-chain programs\n   153→- `packages/vrf/` — VRF client integration\n   154→- `packages/wallet/src/treasury/` — fee constants and treasury logic\n   155→\n   156→This code is deployed on-chain and under active development by the implementation team. Any uncoordinated change — even a comment edit, a Cargo.toml version bump, or a \"cleanup\" — can break builds, invalidate deployed program hashes, or cause settlement bugs that lose real money.\n   157→\n   158→**If you want on-chain behavior to change**: write a proposal to `docs/proposals/`. Describe what you want, not how to implement it. The implementation team owns all on-chain code.\n   159→\n   160→## Commit Messages\n   161→\n   162→Use conventional commits:\n   163→\n   164→```\n   165→feat(scope): short description\n   166→fix(scope): short description\n   167→docs(scope): short description\n   168→chore(scope): short description\n   169→```\n   170→\n   171→Scope examples: `platform`, `coinflip`, `crash`, `game-engine`, `wallet`, `boss-raid`, `docs`\n   172→\n   173→## Do Not\n   174→\n   175→- **Touch `solana/`, `packages/anchor-client/`, `packages/vrf/`, or `packages/wallet/src/treasury/`** — ever. Write a proposal instead. This is the #1 rule.\n   176→- Implement logic/functionality changes directly — write a proposal to `docs/proposals/`\n   177→- Delete or restructure directories without changelog entry marked Breaking\n   178→- Introduce new packages without documenting in ARCHITECTURE.md\n   179→- Add dependencies without documenting why in the changelog\n   180→- Change `.env` files or deployment configs without noting it\n   181→- Skip the changelog — this is the #2 rule\n   182→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d7619d26-977f-447b-8d13-946b8a80fc7d","uuid":"883f3a94-7703-4550-8552-4b418aba7471","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/CLAUDE.md","content":"# RNG Utopia — Contributor Guide\n\nThis file is auto-loaded by Claude Code. All contributors (human or AI) must follow these rules.\n\n## Who Owns What\n\nThis repo is the **code monorepo**. A separate root repo (not accessible to contributors) holds:\n- Authoritative scope, decisions, and phase boundaries\n- Spec checklists and implementation tracking\n- Verification scripts and project governance\n\n**You can modify any file in this repo**, but you must follow the rules below.\n\n## Changelog Protocol (Mandatory)\n\nEvery batch of work must update `CHANGELOG.md` at the repo root **before committing**.\n\nFormat — append to the top of the Unreleased section:\n\n```markdown\n### YYYY-MM-DD — [Short title]\n**Author**: [name or agent identifier]\n**Scope**: [which areas: docs, platform UI, game-engine, wallet, solana programs, etc.]\n**Changes**:\n- [file or area] — [what changed and why]\n- [file or area] — [what changed and why]\n**Breaking**: [yes/no — did you rename exports, change constants, restructure directories?]\n**Terminology**: [list any term renames, e.g., \"cashback → rakeback\"]\n```\n\nIf `CHANGELOG.md` doesn't exist yet, create it with an `# Changelog` header and `## Unreleased` section.\n\nWhy: The implementation team merges from this repo periodically. The changelog is how they know what to review and reconcile. Skipping it means changes may be reverted.\n\n## Locked Decisions (Do Not Change Without Coordination)\n\nThese are settled. Changing them silently will cause merge conflicts and rework.\n\n| Decision | Current Value | Notes |\n|----------|--------------|-------|\n| Program architecture | Standard Anchor (`#[program]`) | NOT BOLT ECS |\n| Program location | `solana/programs/` | Do not move to root `programs/` |\n| Wallet approach | `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` | No Privy until post-V1 |\n| Fee total | 3% (300 bps) | Hardcoded on-chain |\n| Fee split | 200 rev / 70 rakeback / 30 chest | See terminology below |\n| VRF provider | MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF | For coinflip |\n| FE entrypoint | `apps/platform/` | Other app dirs are scaffolds |\n| Package manager | pnpm | With turborepo |\n\nIf you believe a locked decision should change, add a proposal file to `docs/proposals/` instead of changing the code directly.\n\n## Canonical Terminology\n\nUse these terms consistently in code, comments, docs, and UI labels.\n\n| Correct | Incorrect / Deprecated |\n|---------|----------------------|\n| rakeback pool | cashback pool, daily cashback |\n| chest treasury | rewards budget, daily rewards |\n| RAKEBACK_BPS / RAKEBACK_POOL_BPS | CASHBACK_BPS / CASHBACK_POOL_BPS |\n| CHEST_TREASURY_BPS / CHEST_BPS | REWARDS_BUDGET_BPS / REWARDS_BPS |\n| Emerald (tier 5) | Platinum |\n| champion (avatar, Lv30) | cavalier |\n\nIf you introduce new terminology, document it in the changelog entry.\n\n## Verification Requirements\n\nBefore committing, you **must** pass:\n\n```bash\npnpm lint        # zero errors (warnings OK)\npnpm build:all   # all packages and apps build\n```\n\nIf you modify Solana programs (`solana/` directory), also run:\n\n```bash\ncd solana && cargo check --workspace   # Rust compiles\n```\n\nDo **not** commit if these fail. If you cannot fix a failure you introduced, revert your changes and document the issue in the changelog.\n\n## File Modification Guidelines\n\n### Visual changes — just do it\nCSS, layout, styling, animations, static assets, avatar images, responsive breakpoints. These are low-risk. Make the change, note it in the changelog, commit.\n\n- `apps/platform/src/index.css` and component-scoped styles\n- `apps/platform/public/` — static assets, images\n- Component JSX structure (when purely visual — moving elements, changing labels)\n- `packages/ui/` — shared UI components (visual only)\n\n### Logic / functionality changes — write a proposal first\nAny change that affects **how the game works**, **what gets calculated**, or **what data flows where** must go through a proposal before implementation.\n\nWrite a short PRD-style proposal to `docs/proposals/YYYY-MM-DD-title.md`:\n\n```markdown\n# Proposal: [Title]\n**Date**: YYYY-MM-DD\n**Author**: [name or agent]\n**Area**: [which game/system]\n\n## Problem\n[What's wrong or missing]\n\n## Proposed Change\n[What you want to change — be specific about files, functions, constants]\n\n## Impact\n[What else this affects — other packages, on-chain programs, types]\n\n## Breaking\n[yes/no — does this rename exports, change constants, alter game rules?]\n```\n\nDo NOT implement the change — just write the proposal. The implementation team will review, approve, and integrate.\n\nExamples of \"logic changes\" that need proposals:\n- Changing fee percentages, tier amounts, or XP formulas\n- Adding/removing game phases or settlement steps\n- Modifying payout calculations or reward distribution\n- Restructuring shared type definitions or package exports\n- Changing wallet connection flow or transaction signing\n- Adding new on-chain instructions or modifying existing ones\n\n### Docs and specs — free to modify (follow terminology)\n- `docs/` — game specs, platform docs, stories\n- Follow the canonical terminology table above\n- Note significant content changes in the changelog\n\n### Shared packages — modify with care\nThese are imported across packages. Renaming exports or changing shapes breaks consumers.\n\n- `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts` — type definitions and constants\n- `packages/game-engine/src/index.ts` — public API surface\n- `packages/wallet/src/` — wallet provider and hooks\n- `packages/config/` — shared config\n- `packages/fairness/` — fairness verification logic\n\nRules for shared packages:\n- **Visual/display changes** (label text, formatting) — OK, just changelog it\n- **Logic/data changes** (constants, formulas, type shapes, exports) — write a proposal\n- **Do not delete exports** — deprecate first, note in changelog\n\n### OFF LIMITS — Smart contracts and on-chain code\n\n**Do not modify, create, delete, rename, or restructure any file in these directories. No exceptions.**\n\n- `solana/` — ALL contents: Anchor programs, Rust crates, Cargo files, deploy scripts, tests, configs\n- `packages/anchor-client/` — generated types from on-chain programs\n- `packages/vrf/` — VRF client integration\n- `packages/wallet/src/treasury/` — fee constants and treasury logic\n\nThis code is deployed on-chain and under active development by the implementation team. Any uncoordinated change — even a comment edit, a Cargo.toml version bump, or a \"cleanup\" — can break builds, invalidate deployed program hashes, or cause settlement bugs that lose real money.\n\n**If you want on-chain behavior to change**: write a proposal to `docs/proposals/`. Describe what you want, not how to implement it. The implementation team owns all on-chain code.\n\n## Commit Messages\n\nUse conventional commits:\n\n```\nfeat(scope): short description\nfix(scope): short description\ndocs(scope): short description\nchore(scope): short description\n```\n\nScope examples: `platform`, `coinflip`, `crash`, `game-engine`, `wallet`, `boss-raid`, `docs`\n\n## Do Not\n\n- **Touch `solana/`, `packages/anchor-client/`, `packages/vrf/`, or `packages/wallet/src/treasury/`** — ever. Write a proposal instead. This is the #1 rule.\n- Implement logic/functionality changes directly — write a proposal to `docs/proposals/`\n- Delete or restructure directories without changelog entry marked Breaking\n- Introduce new packages without documenting in ARCHITECTURE.md\n- Add dependencies without documenting why in the changelog\n- Change `.env` files or deployment configs without noting it\n- Skip the changelog — this is the #2 rule\n","numLines":182,"startLine":1,"totalLines":182}}}
