{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017GiBK3rMpX5eWtWVUq3YqA","type":"tool_result","content":"   300→        // matchId is the match PDA base58 — fetch to get the creator\n   301→        const matchPda = new PublicKey(matchId);\n   302→        const existingMatch = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n   303→        if (!existingMatch) {\n   304→          setError(\"Match not found. It may have been cancelled.\");\n   305→          return;\n   306→        }\n   307→\n   308→        const matchCreator = new PublicKey(existingMatch.player1);\n   309→        const transaction = await buildJoinMatchTx(\n   310→          connection,\n   311→          publicKey,\n   312→          matchCreator\n   313→        );\n   314→\n   315→        await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n   316→\n   317→        // Clear dismissed ref — this is a new intentional match\n   318→        dismissedMatchRef.current = null;\n   319→\n   320→        // Fetch updated match\n   321→        const updated = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n   322→        if (updated) {\n   323→          setActiveMatch(updated);\n   324→        }\n   325→\n   326→        refreshMatches();\n   327→      } catch (err) {\n   328→        setError(parseTransactionError(err));\n   329→      } finally {\n   330→        setJoining(false);\n   331→        setJoiningMatchId(null);\n   332→      }\n   333→    },\n   334→    [connected, publicKey, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches]\n   335→  );\n   336→\n   337→  const cancelMatch = useCallback(async () => {\n   338→    if (!connected || !publicKey || !activeMatch) {\n   339→      setError(\"No active match to cancel.\");\n   340→      return;\n   341→    }\n   342→\n   343→    setError(null);\n   344→    try {\n   345→      const transaction = await buildCancelMatchTx(connection, publicKey);\n   346→      await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n   347→      setActiveMatch(null);\n   348→      refreshMatches();\n   349→    } catch (err) {\n   350→      setError(parseTransactionError(err));\n   351→    }\n   352→  }, [connected, publicKey, activeMatch, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches]);\n   353→\n   354→  const timeoutCancel = useCallback(async () => {\n   355→    if (!connected || !publicKey || !activeMatch) {\n   356→      setError(\"No active match to cancel.\");\n   357→      return;\n   358→    }\n   359→    if (!activeMatch.player2) {\n   360→      setError(\"Match has no opponent.\");\n   361→      return;\n   362→    }\n   363→\n   364→    setError(null);\n   365→    try {\n   366→      const matchCreator = new PublicKey(activeMatch.player1);\n   367→      const opponent = new PublicKey(activeMatch.player2);\n   368→\n   369→      const transaction = await buildTimeoutCancelTx(\n   370→        connection,\n   371→        publicKey,\n   372→        matchCreator,\n   373→        opponent\n   374→      );\n   375→      await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n   376→      setActiveMatch(null);\n   377→      refreshMatches();\n   378→    } catch (err) {\n   379→      setError(parseTransactionError(err));\n   380→    }\n   381→  }, [connected, publicKey, activeMatch, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches]);\n   382→\n   383→  /** Settle the match on-chain: send payout to winner, close PDA.\n   384→   *  Can be called by either player (winner claims their payout,\n   385→   *  loser triggers it to free the match slot). */\n   386→  const claimPayout = useCallback(async () => {\n   387→    if (!connected || !publicKey || !activeMatch) {\n   388→      setError(\"No active match to claim.\");\n   389→      return;\n   390→    }\n   391→    if (!activeMatch.winner) {\n   392→      setError(\"Match has no winner yet.\");\n   393→      return;\n   394→    }\n   395→\n   396→    setClaiming(true);\n   397→    setError(null);\n   398→    try {\n   399→      const winner = new PublicKey(activeMatch.winner);\n   400→      const matchCreator = new PublicKey(activeMatch.player1);\n   401→      const opponent = activeMatch.player2\n   402→        ? new PublicKey(activeMatch.player2)\n   403→        : PublicKey.default;\n   404→\n   405→      const transaction = await buildClaimPayoutTx(\n   406→        connection,\n   407→        publicKey,   // caller (whoever is clicking — winner or loser)\n   408→        winner,      // payout goes here\n   409→        matchCreator,\n   410→        opponent\n   411→      );\n   412→\n   413→      await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n   414→\n   415→      // Match PDA is now closed — clear local state\n   416→      dismissedMatchRef.current = activeMatch.id;\n   417→      setActiveMatch(null);\n   418→      refreshMatches();\n   419→    } catch (err) {"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d7619d26-977f-447b-8d13-946b8a80fc7d","uuid":"bcdbae34-ff65-4dfb-9bb2-1a704ed76cf3","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx","content":"        // matchId is the match PDA base58 — fetch to get the creator\n        const matchPda = new PublicKey(matchId);\n        const existingMatch = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n        if (!existingMatch) {\n          setError(\"Match not found. It may have been cancelled.\");\n          return;\n        }\n\n        const matchCreator = new PublicKey(existingMatch.player1);\n        const transaction = await buildJoinMatchTx(\n          connection,\n          publicKey,\n          matchCreator\n        );\n\n        await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n\n        // Clear dismissed ref — this is a new intentional match\n        dismissedMatchRef.current = null;\n\n        // Fetch updated match\n        const updated = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n        if (updated) {\n          setActiveMatch(updated);\n        }\n\n        refreshMatches();\n      } catch (err) {\n        setError(parseTransactionError(err));\n      } finally {\n        setJoining(false);\n        setJoiningMatchId(null);\n      }\n    },\n    [connected, publicKey, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches]\n  );\n\n  const cancelMatch = useCallback(async () => {\n    if (!connected || !publicKey || !activeMatch) {\n      setError(\"No active match to cancel.\");\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setError(null);\n    try {\n      const transaction = await buildCancelMatchTx(connection, publicKey);\n      await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n      setActiveMatch(null);\n      refreshMatches();\n    } catch (err) {\n      setError(parseTransactionError(err));\n    }\n  }, [connected, publicKey, activeMatch, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches]);\n\n  const timeoutCancel = useCallback(async () => {\n    if (!connected || !publicKey || !activeMatch) {\n      setError(\"No active match to cancel.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if (!activeMatch.player2) {\n      setError(\"Match has no opponent.\");\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setError(null);\n    try {\n      const matchCreator = new PublicKey(activeMatch.player1);\n      const opponent = new PublicKey(activeMatch.player2);\n\n      const transaction = await buildTimeoutCancelTx(\n        connection,\n        publicKey,\n        matchCreator,\n        opponent\n      );\n      await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n      setActiveMatch(null);\n      refreshMatches();\n    } catch (err) {\n      setError(parseTransactionError(err));\n    }\n  }, [connected, publicKey, activeMatch, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches]);\n\n  /** Settle the match on-chain: send payout to winner, close PDA.\n   *  Can be called by either player (winner claims their payout,\n   *  loser triggers it to free the match slot). */\n  const claimPayout = useCallback(async () => {\n    if (!connected || !publicKey || !activeMatch) {\n      setError(\"No active match to claim.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if (!activeMatch.winner) {\n      setError(\"Match has no winner yet.\");\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setClaiming(true);\n    setError(null);\n    try {\n      const winner = new PublicKey(activeMatch.winner);\n      const matchCreator = new PublicKey(activeMatch.player1);\n      const opponent = activeMatch.player2\n        ? new PublicKey(activeMatch.player2)\n        : PublicKey.default;\n\n      const transaction = await buildClaimPayoutTx(\n        connection,\n        publicKey,   // caller (whoever is clicking — winner or loser)\n        winner,      // payout goes here\n        matchCreator,\n        opponent\n      );\n\n      await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n\n      // Match PDA is now closed — clear local state\n      dismissedMatchRef.current = activeMatch.id;\n      setActiveMatch(null);\n      refreshMatches();\n    } catch (err) {","numLines":120,"startLine":300,"totalLines":500}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011j3hV5bjmCT48TkgDC2Psd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The callers need to be updated:\n\n1. `buildJoinMatchTx` — now takes `oraoTreasury` as 4th arg (line 309-313)\n2. `buildTimeoutCancelTx` — now takes `randomnessAccount` as 5th arg (line 369-374)\n3. `buildClaimPayoutTx` — signature changed: `winner` removed, replaced with `randomnessAccount` as 5th arg (line 405-411)\n\nFor the callers:\n1. `joinMatch`: The caller needs to pass Orao treasury. The treasury can be fetched from the Orao network state account. \n\nFor the other two functions, I need to figure out how to get the `randomnessAccount` (which is the match's `vrfRequestKey`). The `UIMatch` type doesn't currently include this field, even though the on-chain match has `vrf_request_key`. I could either add it to `UIMatch` or fetch the on-chain match data when needed. The simplest approach would be to fetch it inline or derive it from the existing data.\n\nActually, since the randomness account is deterministically derived from the match PDA using the VRF seed, the callers can compute it themselves by exporting the helper functions and having them derive it from the match PDA key. This means I need to export `getOraoRandomnessPda` and update the callers to do the derivation themselves.\n\nFor `joinMatch`, the `oraoTreasury` is the trickier piece — it lives in Orao's NetworkState account, so I could either have callers fetch it from the network or derive it inside the builder function by reading that account directly. I'll simplify this: pass `oraoTreasury` as a parameter to `buildJoinMatchTx` and have the caller fetch it from the Orao network state account, then update both the builder and CoinflipContext to handle the new signature. This is complex. I need to simplify the approach for handling these transaction builders. For `joinMatch`, I'll keep `oraoTreasury` as a parameter and pass a hardcoded Orao treasury address from the caller—this matches the existing pattern in the codebase. For `timeoutCancel` and `claimPayout`, I'll derive the randomness account internally since we already know the match PDA, eliminating the need to pass it separately. I see the issue now — the `randomnessAccount` for timeout and payout operations is actually the VRF request key stored on the match itself, which is derived from the match PDA. Since the program uses the match PDA key as the VRF seed, I can derive it internally rather than passing it as a parameter. So I'll refactor the builders to keep the treasury parameter for `buildJoinMatchTx` since that comes from network state, but have `buildTimeoutCancelTx` and `buildClaimPayoutTx` derive the randomness account internally and remove the winner parameter from the payout builder since that's computed on-chain anyway.\n\nNow I'm updating the chain.ts and CoinflipContext.tsx files...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1506,"cache_read_input_tokens":93207,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1506},"output_tokens":11,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d7619d26-977f-447b-8d13-946b8a80fc7d","uuid":"77a3eab2-6f47-4056-a952-22084e8acdb2"}
